text:
Quite a few people in Japan don't like tomato sauce very much. It's too sour and not sweet enough to counter the acidity. A lot of Japanese tourists to Italy come back dissapointed with the pasta and pizza because they are just not used to the tomato sauce (which is not sweet enough for their palate) which Italy is very big on. 

This is probably why there wasn't enough tomato sauce as you were used to. To the Japanese, tomatoes are a foreign vegetable that doesn't feature in many Japanese dishes. You will also find that a lot of delivery pizza catered to the Japanese palate are not tomato sauce based.

Tomato ketchup, however, is popular because it is sweet and salty like the way most Japanese dishes are seasoned.
